      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">What Is Oxyphenbutazone?</h2>
      <p>Before it became Scrabble legend, oxyphenbutazone was a real medication. It's a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID) that was widely prescribed in the 1950s and 1960s for conditions like arthritis, gout, and rheumatic disorders. The drug was eventually withdrawn from many markets due to serious side effects including blood disorders, but its name lived on in a completely different arena — the Scrabble board.</p>

      <!-- Chemical Name Breakdown -->
